item.title: If I Wrote Sarah Palin's Speech
item.description: Excerpt: . . . They say I lack experience. They’re right, in a way. I have no experience wandering a city for three years trying to find myself. No, I’ve never had that luxury. But Barack Obama has. And I have no experience funneling money from an educational trust into organizations run by my close friend, the convicted terrorist. No experience at all. Nor do I have the experience of having a political career launched by a pair of terrorists who tried to blow up the Capitol and the Pentagon, who succeeded in killing a police officer.
